This paper deals with ethical issues surrounding AI, specifically in the context of autonomous vehicles facing moral dilemmas. It proposes a privacy-preserving crowd-guided AI decision-making approach, which involves differential privacy and perturbation techniques to protect the privacy of voters' data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
